{
  "texts": [
    "First, we examine whether the generated Graphviz code forms a valid graph G h in terms of the DOT language.",
    "This is done by simply processing with the pydot library foot_2.",
    "Nodes alignment by bipartite matching.",
    "Second, we extract nodes V h from G h and align them with nodes from the reference graph: V r from G r using the similarity of the texts in nodes.",
    "For this node alignment, we apply the bipartite matching problem for the two sets of nodes V h and V r, using the similarity function sim(v r, v h) between two texts in the reference v r ∈ V r and hypothesis nodes v h ∈ V h with a textual similarity metric."
  ]
}